Breeding adult.description: White-faced Ibises have a white border that goes all the way around the eye and a bare patch of pink skin in front of the eye that Glossy Ibis do not have.

Nonbreeding adult/immature.description: Immature/nonbreeding White-faced Ibises are very similar to Immature Glossy Ibis and sometimes cannot be separated, especially at a distance. At close range, look for the White-faced Ibis's red eye and the Glossy Ibis's brown eye.

Juvenile.description: Juvenile White Ibises look similar to juvenile Glossy Ibises, but they have white (not dark) underparts.
